festival.introText:
Electric Castle is the first Romanian festival that took electronic dance music and live concerts sounds to a castle’s domain. Since its first edition in 2013, the festival was shortlisted every year for the Best Medium Sized Festival Category at the European Festival Awards, among other important European names.

Held on the domain of Bánffy Castle, Electric Castle Festival is an unique, mind-blowing experience.

It shakes up the way people interact with music by combining a visually innovative concept with an eclectic musical line-up, breaking the boundaries between electronic music and reggae, mainstream and subculture genres.

It’s the only music festival in Romania to offer a complete and authentic experience through notorious international artists, a vast camping area, a diverse food court and exceptional scenery.

faqs.question: When is Electric Castle 2023?
faqs.answer: Electric Castle takes place Wednesday 19th July - Sunday 23rd July 2023.

faqs.question: Where is Electric Castle?
faqs.answer: Electric Castle is located at the Transylvanian domain of Bánffy Castle, near Cluj-Napoca in Romania.

news.title: More acts to added to impressive Electric Castle 2017 line up
news.summary: They join the likes of previously announced Moderat, Alt-J, and Nero at the five-day event in Romania.

news.title: Tickets for Electric Castle 2017 are on sale
news.summary: The festival returns to Banffy Castle between Wednesday 12th and Sunday 16th July. DJ Sneak, Alt-J, Moderat and more have already been added to the bill for 2017.
